<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="870" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">123 [Chase, Augustus S.]: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-18T18:00:00-05:00">April 18,
                                1946—6 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>7. Text your telegram has been repeated Chungking with Dept’s approval in
                        principle (Urtel 26, Apr 15) but with final authority resting with General
                        Marshall.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>